  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2018-06-27",
    "date": "2019-09-04T19:19:27Z",
    "text": "Social Security Administration Fairness Act \n\nThis bill (1) provides funding for certain administrative expenses of the Social Security Administration (SSA); (2) makes individuals\u00a0eligible to receive Old Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance (OASDI) benefits beginning in the first month of disability; (3) eliminates the Medicare waiting period for recipients of OASDI benefits; and (4) requires the SSA to satisfy certain public-notice and reporting requirements before closing or consolidating a field office or hearing office."
  },
